==English==
===Noun===
'''[[stud]] [[muffin]]'''
# a very attractive man
===Quotations===
*'''1995''': ''Billboard'' magazine quoted an Oklahoma City radio program who described him as "a stud muffin" &mdash; "there was just a vibe on this guy out there, especially among women" (Stark 1992, 89) &mdash; Curtis W Ellison, ''Country Music Culture: From Hard Times to Heaven'', University Press of Mississippi, 1995, page 44
*'''1999''': "I'm a total '''stud muffin'''.  Can't you see it?" Simon joked. &mdash; John W Milor, ''Apparition', 1999, page 106
*'''2003''': “A stud!” “A '''stud muffin'''!” In general, the students’ enthusiasm for Clinton was equalled by their disdain for George W. Bush. &mdash; ''The New Yorker'', 11 August 2003